============================================================
2026-05-18 14:50 UTC — MongoDB systemd service fixed
============================================================
Issue: galaxybot-mongod.service was failing (restart counter 242).
  Root-owned mongod (PID 6037, started by start.sh) held the lock;
  systemd tried to start another as mongodb user and failed.
Fix:
  - Killed root-owned mongod (PID 6037) + stale zombie (PID 8952)
  - chown -R mongodb:mongodb /data/db /var/log/mongodb
  - rm -f /data/db/mongod.lock
  - Started via systemctl start galaxybot-mongod (clean first try)
  - Reset failed restart counter: systemctl reset-failed galaxybot-mongod
  - Restarted galaxybot-server to reconnect
Result: All 3 services now track through systemd properly. Ports 9090,
  9091, 5150, 90, 27017 all listening.

============================================================
2026-05-18 14:50 UTC — start.sh modified
============================================================
Issue: start.sh launched MongoDB directly as root via mongod --fork,
  bypassing systemd and causing the ownership/lock conflict.
Fix: Replaced the direct mongod --fork call with:
    sudo systemctl start galaxybot-mongod
  Now all 3 services start consistently through systemd.

